                                                                              .

@{fg shine}To install...@{fg text}

To install just copy @{fg shine}mGzdIRX@{fg text} to whatever dir on your HD you want
(BBS:utils??) and edit the config file in S: named @{fg shine}mGZdIRx.cFg@{fg text}
like this:

     ----------------[ cut from Magz' config file ]------------------
BBS:2elite/dir1
BBS:2elite/dir2
BBS:2elite/dir3
BBS:3request/dir1
BBS:4amix/dir1
BBS:5ascii/dir1
bbs:6grt/dir1
bbs:7mgs!/dir1
BBS:9school/dir1
@
BBS:2elite/upload/
BBS:2elite/older/
BBS:2elite/old/
BBS:3request/upload/
BBS:4amix/upload/
BBS:5ascii/upload/
bbs:6grt/upload/
bbs:7mgs!/upload/
BBS:9school/upload/
             ----------------[ end of cut ]------------------


       The lines above the @{fg shine}@@{fg text} are the @{fg shine}dirs@{fg text} you want to scan through,
        while the lines below the @{fg shine}@@{fg text} are the @{fg shine}paths@{fg text} the files in your
                              dir<x> may be. 


                              %%% @{fg shine}WARNING@{fg text} %%%
         Remember to write the paths RIGHT and include "@{fg shine}/@{fg text}" or "@{fg shine}:@{fg text}"
         at the end of @{fg shine}EVERY@{fg text} path, or mGzdIRX wont find your files
                 and remove all of them from your dir<x>!!
                              %%% @{fg shine}WARNING@{fg text} %%%




@{"how do I use it then?!" link how 2 use}

